article.headline: Indiana State 70, Coastal Carolina 46
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- David Moss scored 24 points, including 9 of 10 free throws, to lead Indiana State to a 70-46 win Friday night over Coastal Carolina in both teams' season opener. Amani Daanish added 12 points and eight rebounds for Indiana State (1-0), which dominated the game from the tipoff with its defense and forced Coastal Carolina to miss eight of its first nine shots. The Chanticleers (0-1) had 10 first-half turnovers, including three in their first six possessions. Jack Leasure had 16 points to lead Coastal Carolina, which was plagued by 19 turnovers. The Sycamores jumped out to a quick 17-3 lead eight minutes into the contest. Coastal Carolina cut the lead to 11 with 9:01 in the first half, but that was as close as they would get. The Chanticleers' 46 points are the fewest scored by an opponent in an Indiana State win since January 5, 2001, when ISU beat Evansville 45-40.
